who want to save it

00:02:00.140 --> 00:02:03.040 align:middle line:10%
and lending it to businesses
and people who need to borrow?

00:02:03.040 --> 00:02:05.870 align:middle line:10%
Well, not exactly.

00:02:05.870 --> 00:02:08.190 align:middle line:10%
Here's a fact that
not many people know:

00:02:08.190 --> 00:02:11.225 align:middle line:10%
a bank doesn't actually need to
have any real money before it

00:02:11.225 --> 00:02:13.320 align:middle line:10%
can make a loan to someone.

00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:15.185 align:middle line:10%
When you take out a
mortgage from the bank,

00:02:15.185 --> 00:02:17.810 align:middle line:10%
the bank doesn't take that money
from somebody's grandma's life

00:02:17.810 --> 00:02:18.650 align:middle line:10%
savings.

00:02:18.650 --> 00:02:22.140 align:middle line:10%
No, instead they simply
open up a computer and types

00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:23.770 align:middle line:10%
some numbers into your account.

00:02:23.770 --> 00:02:25.860 align:middle line:10%
You get a huge wad of
money in your account,

00:02:25.860 --> 00:02:28.270 align:middle line:10%
and you also get
a huge wad of debt

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:31.270 align:middle line:10%
that you'll be repaying
over the next 25 years.

00:02:31.270 --> 00:02:33.830 align:middle line:10%
But the money that you borrowed
was created out of nothing

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:36.440 align:middle line:10%
and just typed
into your account.

00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:38.030 align:middle line:90%
We know that's hard to believe.

00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:39.970 align:middle line:84%
But you don't need to
take our word for it.

00:02:39.970 --> 00:02:41.490 align:middle line:84%
The Bank of England
themselves say

00:02:41.490 --> 00:02:45.460 align:middle line:84%
that "when banks make loans,
they create additional bank

00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:48.120 align:middle line:84%
deposits for those that
have borrowed the money."

00:02:48.120 --> 00:02:51.530 align:middle line:84%
These bank deposits are just
the numbers in your account.

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:53.500 align:middle line:10%
And Martin Wolf, the
chief economics editor

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:56.350 align:middle line:10%
at "The Financial Times"
says, "The essence

00:02:56.350 --> 00:02:58.010 align:middle line:10%
of the contemporary
monetary system

00:02:58.010 --> 00:03:00.330 align:middle line:10%
is the creation of
money out of nothing

00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:02.950 align:middle line:10%
by private banks,
often foolish lending."

00:03:02.950 --> 00:03:06.080 align:middle line:10%
So almost all the money we
use today is made in this way,

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:10.180 align:middle line:10%
out of nothing, by banks
when they make loans.

00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:11.970 align:middle line:10%
And the only way that
we, as the public,

00:03:11.970 --> 00:03:13.530 align:middle line:10%
can get our hands
on this money is

00:03:13.530 --> 00:03:15.800 align:middle line:10%
to go into debt to the banks.

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:18.230 align:middle line:10%
In other words,
almost every pound

00:03:18.230 --> 00:03:20.990 align:middle line:10%
that we need in the economy
to run shops, businesses,

00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:22.940 align:middle line:10%
factories, schools,
and hospitals

00:03:22.940 --> 00:03:26.330 align:middle line:10%
must first be borrowed by
us from a High Street bank.

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:28.880 align:middle line:84%
And if one person has a
million pounds, the rest of us

00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:32.370 align:middle line:84%
must be a million
pounds in debt.

00:03:32.370 --> 00:03:34.340 align:middle line:84%
If we try not to go into
debt, then the banks

00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:36.500 align:middle line:84%
would be unable to create
money, and the economy

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:38.220 align:middle line:90%
would grind to a halt.

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:40.680 align:middle line:84%
This is effectively a
whole scale privatization

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:41.970 align:middle line:90%
of the power to create money.

00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:43.969 align:middle line:90%
